<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-427-891  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 427 891.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  June 5 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>GE Information connects to MCI E-mail. (General Electric Co. GEInformation Services, MCI Communications Corp.'s MCI Mail service)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Woods, Wendy.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   General Electric Co. GE Information Services (informationservices)MCI Communications Corp. (information services).andO;Ticker:    MCIC.andO;Topic:     Electronic mail systemsCommunications Software.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>GE INFORMATION CONNECTS TO MCI E-MAIL ROCKVILLE, MARYLAND, U.S.A., 1990 JUN 1(NB) -- GE Information Services (GEIS) says it has connected its globalelectronic messaging services to MCI Mail, enabling customers on bothservices to exchange electronic messages for the first time.andM;GEIS' QUIK-COMM System and its EDI-EXPRESS System have been interconnected toMCI Mail's XChange 400 service using the international X.400 standard forconnecting dissimilar messaging systems.andM;X.400 is a set of guidelines for the format, delivery and receipt ofelectronic messages recommended by the international standards organization,the International Telephone and Telegraph Consultative Committee (CCITT).andM;This X.400 interconnection is the third that GEIS has made with other publicelectronic messaging services in the U.S.andP;  GEIS previously announced X.400interconnections between its QUIK-COMM System and Western Union's EasyLinkservice and ATandamp;T Mail.andM;Five other QUIK-COMM System X.400 interconnections to public mail servicesare currently in operation under pilot conditions with a view to futurecommercialization, according to GEIS.andP;  GEIS officers say they are activelyinvolved in the industry forum to develop an electronic directory servicebased on the CCITT X.500 recommendations.andM;In addition to the QUIK-COMM X.400 Access Service, GEIS offers a range ofinterconnections to various private mail systems, including: IBM PROFS, IBMDISOSS, DEC ALL-In-1, VMSMail, Wang OFFICE, IBM AS/400, System/3X, 3COM3+Mail LAN Mail, and Novell CC:Mail Lan Mail.andP;  For further information onQUIK-COMM X.400 Access Service, call GE Information Services at1-800-433-3683 or contact your local GEIS sales office.andM;(Wendy Woods/19900601/Press Contact: Steve Haracznak, GE InformationServices, 301/340-4494)</TEXT></DOC>